	<item>
		<title><![CDATA[A Longer Read]]></title>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://playground.wordpress.net/?p=205</guid>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The final post in the pack is a slightly longer piece, useful for checking line length, paragraph spacing, and how a single post page feels with more than a screenful of text.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Demo content walks a line. Too little of it and the site looks broken — empty archives, lonely menus, templates collapsing around missing elements. Too much and every fresh environment takes minutes to import, which defeats the purpose of spinning sites up on demand.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This pack aims for the small end of useful: enough posts to paginate a listing if the per-page setting is low, enough pages to fill a navigation menu, and enough variety of blocks that a theme's core styles all get exercised at least once.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you need more than this, that is what the full theme unit test data is for.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[A longer multi-paragraph post for checking reading flow.]]></excerpt:encoded>
